150
00:12:17,260 --> 00:12:17,760
Let's begin.

151
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:22,580
Number one, the door of the car needs to be repainted.

152
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:27,620
Number two, the cat of Amy is really friendly.

153
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:32,300
Number three, a friend of me is coming to dinner.

154
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:36,420
Number four, I didn't like the movie end.

155
00:12:36,660 --> 00:12:37,400
It was terrible.

156
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:43,140
Number five, two weeks notice is required to leave your job.

157
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:47,160
Number six, you just need a good night's rest.

158
00:12:48,740 --> 00:12:51,840
Number seven, the tail of my dog is really short.

159
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:57,180
Finally, number eight, she is a very valuable member of our team.

160
00:13:07,420 --> 00:13:08,900
Okay, let's correct these together.

161
00:13:09,680 --> 00:13:13,900
So number one is grammatically correct, the door of the car.

162
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:18,520
However, in everyday English, compound nouns are usually preferred,

163
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:22,040
and it would be much more natural to say the car door.

164
00:13:23,340 --> 00:13:25,440
Now number two would be incorrect.

165
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:29,820
Even though it's grammatically correct, it's very unnatural.

166
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:35,780
In English, we would use the possessive S. Amy's cat is really friendly.

167
00:13:37,060 --> 00:13:39,180
Now number three is incorrect.

168
00:13:39,980 --> 00:13:45,880
We don't say a friend of me, we have to use the possessive pronoun mine.

169
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:49,080
A friend of mine is coming to dinner.

170
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:55,740
Or maybe you switched this and you wrote my friend is coming to dinner,

171
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:57,760
which would also be correct.

172
00:13:58,620 --> 00:14:02,460
Now number four, I didn't like the movie end.

173
00:14:02,940 --> 00:14:04,240
This is very awkward.

174
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:09,460
It sounds more natural to say I didn't like the end of the movie.

175
00:14:10,560 --> 00:14:13,200
Movie end is not a common compound noun in English.

176
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:16,400
It's more typical to say the end of the movie.

177
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:20,800
Number five is correct, two weeks notice.

178
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:26,040
We have the apostrophe after the S because weeks is plural.

179
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:28,300
Number six is also correct.

180
00:14:29,220 --> 00:14:36,620
This time we have the apostrophe before S because night is a singular noun, a good night.

181
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:42,500
Now number seven, while grammatically is correct, it's not natural.

182
00:14:43,140 --> 00:14:47,900
Remember that we use apostrophe S for people and also for animals.

183
00:14:48,660 --> 00:14:51,800
So my dog's tail is really short.

184
00:14:52,180 --> 00:14:54,420
That would be more natural and more common.

185
00:14:54,920 --> 00:14:58,640
And finally, number eight, this is correct.

186
00:14:59,160 --> 00:15:01,520
She is a very valuable member of our team.

187
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:06,300
In this case, we're using of to show membership in a group.

188
00:15:06,860 --> 00:15:10,240
She is one of the members that belong to the team.

